modules.description: This module manages console capabilities for terminal features like ANSI color, UTF-8 output, and virtual terminal control sequences. It provides functions to create console instances with or without virtual terminal support and query their capabilities. Use cases include enabling colored output conditionally, handling Unicode correctly, and controlling terminal formatting in cross-platform CLI applications.

This module provides a cross-platform interface for managing terminal features such as ANSI color, UTF-8 output, and virtual terminal control sequences. It allows creating and querying console instances to enable conditional colored output, handle Unicode correctly, and control terminal formatting. Key operations include console initialization with or without virtual terminal support and capability detection. For example, applications can use it to render colored logs on supported terminals or ensure proper Unicode display across different platforms.
